== Aubergine ==

Preheat your oven to 200 degrees. Cut the @aubergine{1} in half lengthways and then
slice in half lengthways again so that you have four strips. Mix a pinch of @salt{pinch},
the @tandoori masala spice{1%tsp} (use less if you don't like things too spicy) and a glug
of @oil{glug} together in a #small bowl{}. Massage this into your aubergine and then pop
it on a #baking tray{}. Roast for ~{25%minutes} on the middle shelf of your oven.

> Our chef André isn't a vegetarian but his veggie friends absolutely love this dish - he
> makes it whenever they come over - because they demand it!

== Tomato and Coriander Rice ==

Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into small cubes
(½cm is perfect!). Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop into 1cm cubes.
Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} and @ginger{1%small piece} (or use a #garlic press{}
if you have one). Then peel the ginger using the edge of a #spoon{}, and grate.

Put a #saucepan{} on medium heat and add a glug of @oil{glug}. Cook your onion and
pepper for ~{3%minutes} with a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Add your ginger and half your
garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds} more. Stir in the @ground turmeric{1/2%tsp} and
@basmati rice{175%g} and then pour in the @water{350%ml}. Bring to the boil, then stir
in the @vegetable stock pot{1}. Pop the lid on and cook for ~{10%minutes}. After
~{10%minutes}, remove from the heat and leave your rice, with the lid, on to finish
cooking in its own steam for another ~{10%minutes}.

== Nigella Yoghurt and Salsa ==

As your rice cooks, prepare the remaining ingredients. Remove the root from the
@spring onion{3} and finely chop. Cut the @plum tomatoes{1} into quarters. Roughly chop
the @coriander{1/2%bunch} and mix with your spring onion, cherry tomatoes and your
remaining @garlic clove{1}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and keep to one side.
This is your salsa.

Mix the @Greek style natural yoghurt{1} with the @nigella seeds{1/2%tsp}.

== Assembly ==

When your rice is cooked, add half your salsa and gently stir it through your rice.

Serve your spiced aubergine on top of a generous pile of rice and finish with a few
dollops of nigella yoghurt and your remaining salsa.. Yum!